<H1>Help pages for the Online Media Web Browser</H1>
<P>

<H2>Quick guide</H2>


<P>A few quick hints should be enough to allow you to use the browser.

<UL>

<LI>Use <KBD>NEXT PAGE</KBD> and <KBD>PREVIOUS PAGE</KBD> to scroll up
and down the document. 

<LI>If there is anything you can activate on a page then you will see that
one piece of text or an image is highlighted differently to the others
(the exact colour may vary from page to page).

<LI>Pressing <KBD>SELECT</KBD> will activate the highlighted item.

<LI>If this is a link then the browser will jump to the link (if it is
in the same document) or start to download the new document.

<LI>If it is a map then a cross-hair will appear, see the detailed
description of <A HREF="#map">map mode</A> below.

<LI>Other types of objects are parts of FORMS. These are only useable
with a keyboard.

<LI>To move the highlight around the screen use the <KBD>LEFT</KBD> and 
<KBD>RIGHT</KBD> keys.

<LI>Press <KBD>STATUS</KBD> to see information about the document being
displayed.

<LI>To exit the browser then <KBD>HOME</KBD> to return to the initial
page and then press <KBD>HOME</KBD> again.

</UL>

<P><HR><P>

<H2>The keys in detail</H2>

<P>
A detailed list of the actions of the different keys follows.

<P>
<H3>Control keys</H3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>HELP</kbd>
<DD>Display this page.

<DT><kbd>STATUS</kbd>
<DD>Toggle the <A HREF="#status">status bar</A> at the bottom of the
screen.

<DT><kbd>HOME</kbd>
<DD>Return to the start page. If pressed on the start page then
exit from the browser.

<DT><kbd>BACK</kbd>
<DD>If a <a href="#menu">menu</a> is being displayed then this will
close the menu. If the highlight is in <a href="#map">map mode</a>
then this will return to standard mode. If the caret is active then
this will remove the caret and return to normal highlighting mode.
Otherwise it will take you back to the page last visited.

<DT><kbd><A NAME="select">SELECT</A></kbd>
<DD>This will activate the selected item. The actions depend on 
the type of the item.
When over a link this will activate the link. When over a map 
it will enter <a href=#map>map mode</a>.

</DL>

<HR>

<H3>Cursor keys</H3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>UP</kbd>
<DD>Move highlight up the screen.

<DT><kbd>DOWN</kbd>
<DD>Move highlight down the screen.

<DT><kbd>RIGHT</kbd>
<DD>Move highlight to the next useable item visible on the screen.

<DT><kbd>LEFT</kbd>
<DD>Move highlight to the previous useable item visible on the screen.

<DT><kbd>UP RIGHT</kbd>
<DD>Scroll up the document by a screen.

<DT><kbd>DOWN RIGHT</kbd>
<DD>Scroll down the document by a screen.

<DT><kbd>UP LEFT</kbd>
<DD>Unused.

<DT><kbd>DOWN LEFT</kbd>
<DD>Unused.

</DL>

<HR>

<H3>VCR control keys</H3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>REWIND</kbd>
<DD>Scroll up the document by a line.

<DT><kbd>PLAY</kbd>
<DD>Unused.

<DT><kbd>FAST FORWARD</kbd>
<DD>Scroll down the document by a line.

<DT><kbd>PREVIOUS PAGE</kbd>
<DD>Scroll up the document by a screen.

<DT><kbd>STOP</kbd>
<DD>Abort the downloading of the current document.

<DT><kbd>NEXT PAGE</kbd>
<DD>Scroll down document by a screen.

<DT><kbd>PAUSE</kbd>
<DD>Reload the current document.

</DL>

<HR>

<H3>Fastext keys</H3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>RED</kbd>
<DD>Load the hotlist.

<DT><kbd>GREEN</kbd>
<DD>Enter a new URL (requires a keyboard).

<DT><kbd>YELLOW</kbd>
<DD>Scroll the document to the left.

<DT><kbd>BLUE</kbd>
<DD>Scroll the document to the right.

</DL>

<HR>

<H3>Number keys</H3>

<DL>

<DT><kbd>1</kbd>
<DD>Simple information mode. Only show document title on the status bar.

<DT><kbd>2</kbd>
<DD>Medium information mode. Show document URL on the status bar.

<DT><kbd>3</kbd>
<DD>High information mode. Show link URL's and connection messages on
the status bar.

<DT><kbd>8</kbd>
<DD>Toggle document background and colours on and off. Some colour choices
can be very difficult to read either due to being viewed on a television
set or due to bad page design. This option allows you display the text
in the default black on grey.

<DT><kbd>9</kbd>
<DD>Toggle anti-twitter filter. This is available to show the difference
the filter makes.

</DL>

<P>
<HR>

<P>
<H3><a name=map>Maps</a></H3>
<P>
When a map is selected a blue cross-hair will appear. The 8 cursor keys
can be used to move this cross-hair around. A single press is all that
is needed to start the cross-hair moving in the given direction, the key
needn't be held down. Pressing any other cursor key will change the
direction of travel accordingly. Pressing <KBD>SELECT</KBD>
whilst the cross-hair is moving will stop it. Pressing it again will
select that map location.

<HR>
<H3><a name=menu>Menus</a></H3>
<P>
When a menu is up you can use the <KBD>UP</KBD> and <KBD>DOWN</KBD> keys to 
move the highlight box through the list. Press <KBD>SELECT</KBD> to toggle
an item on and off and then press <KBD>BACK</KBD> to close the menu.

<HR>
<a name=status><H3>Status bar</H3></a>
<P>
The status bar has four areas showing:
<OL>
	<LI>The type of the highlighted item.
	<LI>The title of the document.
	<LI>A scroll bar showing the visible area of the document.
	<LI>The status of the current fetch.
</OL>
<HR>
<P>
Press <KBD>BACK</kbd> to return to the previous page.
<P>
</BODY>
